.\" Manpage for auru.
.\" Contact nicolascarolo.dev@gmail.com to correct errors or typos.
.TH auru 8 "4 April 2020" "0.5.1" "auru man page"
.SH NAME
auru \- update AUR packages
.SH SYNOPSIS
auru <operation>
.SH DESCRIPTION
auru is a shell tool for keeping up-to-date AUR packages on Arch Linux.
.SH OPERATIONS
.TP
.B -B, --build
Build an AUR package when its repository is already downloaded, but the package is not yet installed
.TP
.B -Q, --query
List all installed AUR packages
.TP
.B -R, --remove
Remove an AUR package
.TP
.B -S, --sync
Check whether an AUR package is available and install it
.TP
.B -U, --upgrade
Check whether there are available updates for all AUR packages or for a specific package. This function
can also be used for updating auru, running the command as root and specifing 'auru' as package
.TP
.B -V, --version
Show information on the version of the software
.TP
.B -h, --help
Show available commands and their syntax
.SH OPTIONS
auru does not take any options
.SH SEE ALSO
GitHub page of the project <https://github.com/nicolas-carolo/auru>
.SH REPORTING BUGS
Nothing
